Loxostege turbidalis is a species of moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Treitschke in 1829. It is found in most of Europe, except Ireland, Great Britain, Norway, the Benelux and the Iberian Peninsula. It has also been recorded from Russia, Turkey, China and Japan.The wingspan is 28–33 millimetres (1.1–1.3 in). Adults are on wing in June and July.The larvae feed on Artemisia species.